Package org.bukkit.material

Interface Colorable

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    Bed, Sheep, Shulker, Sign
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Dye, Wool
    public interface Colorable
    An object that can be colored.

    • Method Detail

      • getColor

        @Nullable
DyeColor getColor()
        Gets the color of this object.
        This may be null to represent the default color of an object, if the object has a special default color (e.g Shulkers).
        Returns:
        The DyeColor of this object.

      • setColor

        void setColor​(DyeColor color)
        Sets the color of this object to the specified DyeColor.
        This may be null to represent the default color of an object, if the object has a special default color (e.g Shulkers).
        Parameters:
        color - The color of the object, as a DyeColor.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if argument is null and this implementation does not support null
